The existing workaround using `--mdcomments` is the quickest fix. Here's a bit more context on the root cause and the proper XML solution:

**Why this happens**

XML normalises whitespace in text nodes — consecutive whitespace (including newlines) in `<summary>` text is folded into a single space. So blank lines between paragraphs in your XML doc comments are silently discarded.

**Proper XML doc solution: use `(para)` tags**

The XML documentation schema supports explicit paragraph breaks via `(para)`:

```fsharp
/// <summary>
/// First paragraph.
///
/// (para)Second paragraph, separated by para tag.(/para)
///
/// (para)Third paragraph.(/para)
/// </summary>
```

FSharp.Formatting renders `(para)` elements as separate `<p>` tags in the API reference, which preserves your intended paragraph structure without requiring `--mdcomments` mode.

**`--mdcomments` mode**

If switching to `(para)` tags is impractical for an existing codebase, `--mdcomments` (which renders XML doc text as Markdown) is the pragmatic alternative — double blank lines become paragraph breaks as you'd expect.

The trade-off: `--mdcomments` doesn't mix well with structured XML tags like `(paramref)`, `(see cref="...")`, etc. If you use those heavily, `(para)` tags are the safer choice.

