This is a long-standing enhancement request! Since 2013, browser support for the Clipboard API has improved dramatically. Today, the standard approach is a small "Copy" button per code block using:

```javascript
navigator.clipboard.writeText(codeBlock.textContent)
```

This API is supported in all modern browsers (Chrome 66+, Firefox 63+, Safari 13.1+, Edge 79+) and works without any special permissions on pages served over HTTPS.

**Implementation sketch** (could go in `fsdocs-default.js` or a `(script)` in the template):
```javascript
document.querySelectorAll('pre > code').forEach(function(codeBlock) {
  var button = document.createElement('button');
  button.className = 'copy-code-button';
  button.textContent = 'Copy';
  button.addEventListener('click', function() {
    navigator.clipboard.writeText(codeBlock.textContent).then(function() {
      button.textContent = 'Copied!';
      setTimeout(function() { button.textContent = 'Copy'; }, 2000);
    });
  });
  codeBlock.parentElement.style.position = 'relative';
  codeBlock.parentElement.insertBefore(button, codeBlock);
});
```

Paired with a little CSS to position the button in the top-right corner of the `<pre>` block, this would be a clean, modern solution. There's no new dependency required — just a small addition to the existing JS/CSS template files.

If someone wants to pick this up, it would be a self-contained and welcome contribution!

